ExtraTexts.UntranslatedText:
Welcome to Quantum Console! In order to see specific help about any specific command, please use the 'manual' command. Use 'help manual' to see more about the manual command. To see a full list of all commands, use 'all-commands'.

mono-targets
Various commands may show a mono-target in their command signature.
This means they are not static commands, and instead requires instance(s) of the class in order to invoke the command.
Each mono-target works differently as follows:
 - single: uses the first instance of the type found in the scene
 - all: uses all instances of the type found in the scene
 - registry: uses all instances of the type found in the registry
 - singleton: creates and manages a single instance automatically

The registry is a part of the Quantum Registry that allows you to decide which specific instances of the class should be used when invoking the command. In order to add an object to the registry, either use Hikaria.QC.QuantumRegistry.RegisterObject<T> or the runtime command 'register-object<T>'.

Languages.English:
Welcome to Quantum Console! In order to see specific help about any specific command, please use the 'manual' command. Use 'help manual' to see more about the manual command. To see a full list of all commands, use 'all-commands'.

mono-targets
Various commands may show a mono-target in their command signature.
This means they are not static commands, and instead requires instance(s) of the class in order to invoke the command.
Each mono-target works differently as follows:
 - single: uses the first instance of the type found in the scene
 - all: uses all instances of the type found in the scene
 - registry: uses all instances of the type found in the registry
 - singleton: creates and manages a single instance automatically

The registry is a part of the Quantum Registry that allows you to decide which specific instances of the class should be used when invoking the command. In order to add an object to the registry, either use Hikaria.QC.QuantumRegistry.RegisterObject<T> or the runtime command 'register-object<T>'.
Languages.Chinese:
欢迎使用量子控制台！为了查看有关任何特定指令的帮助，请使用'manual'指令。使用'help manual'可以查看更多关于 man 指令的信息。要查看所有指令的完整列表，请使用'all-commands'。

mono-targets
各种指令可能会在其指令签名中显示一个 mono-target。这意味着它们不是静态指令，而是需要实例化类的实例才能调用该指令。
每个 mono-target 的工作方式如下：
 - single：使用场景中找到的第一个类型实例
 - all：使用场景中所有类型实例
 - registry：使用注册表中的所有类型实例
 - singleton：自动创建和管理一个单一实例

注册表是量子注册表的一部分，允许你决定在调用指令时使用特定的类实例。要将对象添加到注册表中，可以使用 Hikaria.QC.QuantumRegistry.RegisterObject<T> 或运行时指令 register-object<T>。
